agencies;

•influence by, or competition from, third parties with respect to pending, new, or existing contracts with government customers;

•changes in political or social attitudes with respect to security or data privacy issues;

•potential delays or changes in the government appropriations or procurement processes, including as a result of events such as war, including the ongoing conflicts in Ukraine, the Middle East, and Africa, incidents of terrorism, natural disasters, and public health concerns or epidemics; and

